description: Aspose.Diagram is a class library for working with Microsoft Visio files. It allows developers to create new diagrams and work with VSD, VSS, VST, VSX, VTX, VDW and VDX files on ASP.NET web applications, web services and Windows applications. It allows you to open files and manipulate the elements of the diagram, from lines and fills, to more complex elements, and then export to VDX, VSX, VTX, XPS, HTML, SVG, SWF, image or PDF formats.
releaseNotes:
This release introduces the features, enhancements and bug fixes as detailed below:
	Features
DIAGRAM-33197 - Rendering diagram to SWF format
DIAGRAM-33200 - Support Shape.ConnectedShapes(Flags, CategoryFilter) function

Enhancements
DIAGRAM-33199 - [Support Visio Viewer] Output is incorrect when we open VDX in Visio Viewer
DIAGRAM-33222 - Add possibility to include SWF Viewer in output SWF file
DIAGRAM-33221 - Some closed figures are not filled when rendering to SWF

Bugs
DIAGRAM-33180 - [PDF rendering] Font is different in source VSD and output PDF
DIAGRAM-33179 - [PDF rendering] Extra whitespace at the start of page
DIAGRAM-33202 - UML diagram rendering issues
summary: Aspose.Diagram is a class library for working with Microsoft Visio files.
title: Aspose.Diagram for .NET
